# ── linux-libc-dev kernel CVEs (NOT exploitable in Docker containers) ───────
# These are all Linux kernel vulnerabilities found in the Debian 13 base image
# (php:8.2-apache). Docker containers share the HOST kernel — the linux-libc-dev
# package only provides kernel header files for compilation, NOT the running
# kernel. These CVEs require:
#   - Direct access to host kernel (not available in containers)
#   - Specific hardware (GPU, NIC, PCI devices) not present in containers
#   - Ability to mount arbitrary filesystems (blocked in containers)
#   - Kernel module loading privileges (blocked in containers)
#
# These will be resolved when the Debian base image is updated. The container
# runs as an unprivileged Apache process with no kernel access.
#
# Fix available: linux-libc-dev 6.12.69-1 (installed: 6.12.63-1)
# Will auto-resolve when php:8.2-apache rebuilds with updated Debian packages.

