# ── vendor/mockery/mockery/docs/requirements.txt ────────────────────────────
# These CVEs are in a Python requirements.txt file inside the docs/ directory
# of the Mockery PHP test-only library (vendor/mockery/mockery). This file:
#   - Is documentation for the Mockery project itself, not our code
#   - Contains Python dependencies we never install or run (our stack has no Python)
#   - Lives in vendor/ which is NEVER deployed to production (gitignored)
#   - Has zero exploitability in our context (wrong language, wrong environment)
# These are false positives for our threat model. The mockery/mockery package
# is a dev-only dependency used only in PHPUnit tests.
